    <note type="biography">
        <p>American entomologist. Son of John Eatton Le Conte. Trained as a physician but never practised. Published in many fields of natural history, with a particular interest in geographical distribution. Served with the army medical corps during the American Civil War. President, American Association for the Advancement of Science, 1874. Chief clerk to the United States Mint at Philadelphia from 1878.</p></note>
